#
# ENC-2 (double-BOM): the `bom_tagged_roundtrips_redetect_stably` counterexample
# s = "\u{feff}\u{feff}". The FIRST U+FEFF is the encoding MARKER; the SECOND is
# CONTENT. The old `decode`/`decode_with` double-stripped the BOM (once via
# `Encoding::for_bom` length-slicing, once via `Encoding::decode`'s own internal
# BOM sniffing), eroding one content U+FEFF per decode pass — so re-detection was
# non-idempotent and the round-trip silently lost data. Fixed by decoding the
# post-marker body with `decode_without_bom_handling`.
#
# This case is pinned DETERMINISTICALLY (not as a random `cc` RNG seed, which the
# fix means proptest can no longer regenerate) by the explicit non-proptest tests
# `double_bom_*` in this file and `encoding::tests::double_bom_*` in the crate, so
# it can never silently disappear regardless of proptest's seed stream.
